      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: reload Codex daemon after account promotion",
        "body": "## Summary\n- restart a running Codex app-server daemon after promoting a managed account into the live system account\n- preserve remote-control mode by using `codex remote-control start` when daemon settings enable it\n- keep normal account-switcher selection display-only; only the existing `System Account` submenu mutates live auth\n- tell the user that Codex CLI changes immediately and the desktop app must be reopened\n\n## Current-main rewrite\nThe original branch predated the current managed-account architecture and conflicted broadly. Its core `System Account` promotion flow has since landed independently. This rewrite keeps only the remaining daemon-reload behavior as one current-main commit, preserving contributor credit.\n\nThe implementation reuses CodexBar's shared bounded `SubprocessRunner` instead of adding another process implementation. Missing CLI and non-running daemon states stay best-effort. A failed restart is reported as partial success because live auth has already changed; account-scoped state is still refreshed before the error reaches the UI.\n\n## Proof\n- exact candidate: `fe76c680502a77a231425e4e4e0df6762d9b3abb`\n- `swift test --filter 'CodexAppServerDaemonReloaderTests|CodexAccountPromotionServiceTests|CodexSystemPromotionUITests|StatusMenuCodexSwitcherTests'`: 55 tests passed\n- `swift build -c release`: green\n- `make check`: green; 20 app catalogs checked against 1,077 English keys; SwiftFormat clean; SwiftLint 0 violations\n- all 21 app locale files include the three new account-switch messages\n- exact-head autoreview: clean (0.78)\n- local installed Codex CLI confirms `app-server daemon version`, `app-server daemon restart`, and `remote-control start` are current commands\n\n## Live boundary\nThe contributor's earlier redacted real-app proof remains useful for the account-promotion workflow, but it predates this rewrite. Exact-head daemon behavior is covered through injected command/regression tests. No local daemon was running during maintainer validation, so no production daemon or live auth was mutated.\n",
